<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="sharpen-vt">sharpen <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'ʃɑːpən/    美 /'ʃɑːrpən/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>削尖；磨快：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>sharpen a pencil
削铅笔</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They also made tools of bones and sharpened stones.
他们还用骨头和磨尖的石头制作工具。</p><footer>外研⑦ – 6</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>使提高；使改进：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Debates sharpen one’s wits.
辩论增长才智。</p></div></div>